```julia
function timezone_bumper(dt, bump = 3)
    if !isa(dt, DateTime))
        throw(ArgumentError("Input must be a DateTime type."))
    end

    return dt + bump * Hour()
end
```

This function `timezone_bumper` takes a `DateTime` as input and adds the specified hours (default is 3). It throws an error if the input is not of `DateTime` type.
